SIMPLE: juror
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Juror
<hw>Ju"ror</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>jureur</ets>
one who takes oath, L. <ets>jurator</ets> a swearer, fr.
<ets>jurare</ets>, <ets>jurari</ets>, to swear. See <er>Jury</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A member of a jury; a
juryman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall both find your lordship judge and <qex>juror</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of any jury for awarding prizes,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jury</ent>⟦br⟧
